title: NASA.Space.Shuttle.STS-119.Launch.2009-03-15.H264-fnoRd.avi
description:
NASA TV recording of the space shuttle Discovery launch coverage for mission STS-119.

Recording begins during the white room procedure where the astronauts enter the orbiter and ends some hours after launch, so it includes final parts of the launch preparation process, the launch itself, coverage of the first flight hours, the press conference summarizing the launch, multiple launch replays from different camera views as well as verious mission control room footage.

Total playback time is 09:43:30, the launch itself is at 03:27:23.

Video codec: h.264
Audio codec: mp3

Information on the STS-119 mission can be found at the nasa website: http://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/shuttle/shuttlemissions/sts119/119_overview.html
